Jessica Amadi, the media officer of Port Harcourt-based Rivers Angels has urged Super Falcons coach Randy Waldrum to invite players of the Nigerian champions as well as that of other Nigeria Women’s Football League clubs for the upcoming US invitational tourney, The PUNCH reports. The Falcons are billed to play Portugal, Trinidad and Tobago and the United States female national teams in the invitational scheduled for June 10 to 16. Angels won the recent Super Six tournament to emerge champions and are set to compete in the West African Football Union Women’s Football ‘B’, which serves as qualifiers for the inaugural CAF Women’s Champions League. “Imagine that a player like Rivers Angels’ highest goal scorer Oghenebrume Ikhekua is invited for the Falcons games in the US, alongside other promising players in the NWFL. It will be a big boost for the domestic league,” Amadi said. On the CAF Women’s Champions League qualifiers, she added, “Nigeria cannot be a pushover in the WAFU B tournament. As the league winners, we are ready to represent the nation to the best of our abilities by winning our games and qualifying.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com